<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[688,969,1806,1832]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bicristatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[688,969,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">Vestinautilus bicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[976,1069,1806,1832]" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1171,1806,1832]" name="Algeria" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">Algeria</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="86" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[227,341,1871,1897]" box="[227,341,1871,1897]" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1871,1897]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1871,1897]" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[227,1436,1918,2015]" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">
In the description of the nautiloids from the Dalle à 
<taxonomicName authority=", Korn et al. (2022)" authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2022" box="[877,1265,1918,1944]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Prolecanitidae" genus="Merocanites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[877,1023,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">Merocanites</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Korn D. &amp; Miao L. &amp; Bockwinkel J." box="[1041,1265,1918,1944]" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" pagination="104 - 129" refId="ref18166" refString="Korn D., Miao L. &amp; Bockwinkel J. 2022. The nautiloids from the Dalle a Merocanites of Timimoun (Tournaisian - Visean boundary, Algeria). European Journal of Taxonomy 789: 104 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2022.789.1635" type="journal article" year="2022">
Korn 
<emphasis box="[1113,1176,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">et al.</emphasis>
(2022)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
discussed the relationships between the genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ryckholt" authorityYear="1852" box="[636,786,1953,1979]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,786,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">Vestinautilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1953" box="[853,1045,1953,1979]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koninckioceratidae" genus="Subvestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="18" pageNumber="85" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[853,1045,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="85">Subvestinautilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they considered the latter as a junior synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[224,1436,303,435]" pageId="19" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ryckholt" authorityYear="1852" box="[227,377,303,329]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="19" pageNumber="86" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,377,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="86">Vestinautilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other genera of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1884" box="[859,1058,303,329]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="19" pageNumber="86" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Trigonoceratidae</taxonomicName>
by the rather weakly ornamented shell in combination with a rounded-triangular or trapezoidal whorl profile. However, it should be noted that some of these genera, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1893" box="[641,757,374,399]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Rineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="19" pageNumber="86" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[641,757,374,399]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="86">Rineceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ryckholt" authorityYear="1852" box="[773,923,373,399]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="19" pageNumber="86" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[773,923,373,399]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="86">Vestinautilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1884" box="[983,1123,373,399]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroboceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="19" pageNumber="86" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[983,1123,373,399]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="86">Stroboceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, show quite similar conch and ornamentat morphology at the beginning of their occurrence in the Tournaisian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
